p%3A%2F%2Fwww.spitzer.caltech.edu%2Fuploaded_files%2Fgraphics%2Fhigh_definition_graphics%2F0011%2F0004%2Fssc2017-01i_Inline.jpg%3F1487786608&h=0da71882&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"f4cd6cc1396c8bb6e33c0533fba0cf595276ce91","tid":130990,"uid":26506,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-22T18:27:48.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>咁近唔怕抄埋一碟<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\nSame 第一反應想睇咩構造 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/biggrin.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/banghead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"81acba374ac0e11cc8a32c56b5ad344cf78cd47a","tid":130990,"uid":47309,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-22T18:29:21.000Z","msg":"頭果兩粒咁大咁近<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/@.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"7abf7f86a6eb8db14c9e1a30d524913e59f0d4f0","tid":130990,"uid":33848,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T01:04:43.000Z","msg":"香港無人理<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"ee8b92f86d9cdba83e5a9a2c5e8acb2fee921797","tid":130990,"uid":33848,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T01:05:07.000Z","msg":"1) Spitzer detects 7 earth size planets around the TRAPPIST-1 Star System<br />\n2) 40 light years away<br />\n3) 3 planets are in the right zone for liquid water<br />\n4) Have measured the masses and radi of earth-size planets<br />\n5) Can look at atmosphere and bio-signatures<br />\n6) Planets are close to each other, you would see them similarly as you would see Earth&rsquo;s moon.<br />\n7) Planets are so close, they interact gravitationally on each other.<br />\n8) Trappist-1e is very close in size to earth. It receives a similar amount of light as Earth does.<br />\n9) Trappist-1f (MIGHT) be water-rich and similar in size as earth (NASA just said currently no detection of water). Receives about as much light as Mars.<br />\n10)Trappist-1g is largest in the system, 13% larger radius than Earth. Receives about as much light as Mars and the Asteroid belt."},{"pid":"f6fa2f418efca2484c1dbb5c2a064d794e1f5985","tid":130990,"uid":77196,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T01:06:19.000Z","msg":"唔講飛過去要幾耐嘅問題...淨係討論下整飛行器要幾耐..."},{"pid":"c6e490965c55f519f13f3d847c304b74bac54c1f","tid":130990,"uid":35347,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T01:06:32.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>香港無人理<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n連登仔：又唔係發現外星人<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/z.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0a143ec0df1dabde392f39eb42c67b33fc15d50c","tid":130990,"uid":19213,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T01:13:37.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>1) Spitzer detects 7 earth size planets around the TRAPPIST-1 Star System<br />\n2) 40 light years away<br />\n3) 3 planets are in the right zone for liquid water<br />\n4) Have measured the masses and radi of earth-size planets<br />\n5) Can look at atmosphere and bio-signatures<br />\n6) Planets are close to each other, you would see them similarly as you would see Earth&rsquo;s moon.<br />\n7) <span style=\"color: red;\">Planets are so close, they interact gravitationally on each other.</span><br />\n8) Trappist-1e is very close in size to earth. It receives a similar amount of light as Earth does.<br />\n9) Trappist-1f (MIGHT) be water-rich and similar in size as earth (NASA just said currently no detection of water). Receives about as much light as Mars.<br />\n10)Trappist-1g is largest in the system, 13% larger radius than Earth. Receives about as much light as Mars and the Asteroid belt.</blockquote><br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n彗星之類軌跡睇落好似好難估計<br />\n仲有會唔會住兩三年之後成粒行星飛左出去宜居帶"},{"pid":"b83d6c8c97cc6915864825eddf2cb23bb4bb0fb7","tid":130990,"uid":24730,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T01:38:26.000Z","msg":"今日準時番咗工<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2976b85db5d6e65545d538e948dff9a5e269c17e","tid":130990,"uid":24345,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T01:52:41.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 如果兩粒咁近都有生命，兩個星球應該可以好早已經接觸對方嘅情況下，唔知文明、科技等會唔會發展得快好多"},{"pid":"9dc21ada434d4d5e026d08e352b77fb18cc0adcf","tid":130990,"uid":54437,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T01:55:30.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 如果兩粒咁近都有生命，兩個星球應該可以好早已經接觸對方嘅情況下，唔知文明、科技等會唔會發展得快好多</blockquote><br />\n可能一早滅左對方<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b8ab6352fb160af2f68ab24358c525d8b663daac","tid":130990,"uid":44569,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T02:26:31.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 如果兩粒咁近都有生命，兩個星球應該可以好早已經接觸對方嘅情況下，唔知文明、科技等會唔會發展得快好多</blockquote><br />\n可能一早滅左對方<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n40 年應該變化不大"},{"pid":"be839104f2c8612b41491c33c538da62421be6e5","tid":130990,"uid":22876,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T02:29:27.000Z","msg":"美國航太總署（NASA）和比利時研究團隊周三（22日）宣布這個消息，<span style=\"color: red;\">這7顆行星位於水瓶座，大小、質量與地球差不多，半徑約地球的0.8至1.1倍，質量約地球的0.4至1.4倍。</span>它們環繞「TRAPPIST-1」，距離地球約39光年（約368.94兆公里）。這個發現讓天文學家都十分雀躍，對於在太陽系外尋找外星生物，可能比預期得要快燃起希望。這也是第一次發現這麼多顆「可能有生命的行星」環繞同一顆恆星。<br />\n<br />\n「Trappist-1」比木星稍大一點，亮度比太陽還弱2千倍，由於這顆恆星小又冷，讓環繞它的7顆行星相當溫和，意味著可能蘊藏液態水，甚至是生命體。研究人員指，7顆中有3顆行星位於適居帶，其中行星「Trappist-1f」最有可能孕育生命體。雖然它的氣溫比地球還低一點，但若有適當的大氣層和足夠的溫室氣體就有可能宜居。<br />\n<br />\n瑞士伯爾尼大學教授德莫里（Brice-Olivier Demory）認為，<span style=\"color: red;\">這七顆行星是迄今尋找外星生命的首選。</span> 而參與研究的比利時列日大學天體物理學家吉倫（Michael Gillon）則相信，「Trappist-1」周圍可能有更多行星。（國際中心／綜合外電報導）<br />\n<br />\n好似真係好屈機 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c1c5b3fe0432b05659c086d7cedc9f4f1ea07a0c","tid":130990,"uid":47309,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T02:35:16.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>美國航太總署（NASA）和比利時研究團隊周三（22日）宣布這個消息，<span style=\"color: red;\">這7顆行星位於水瓶座，大小、質量與地球差不多，半徑約地球的0.8至1.1倍，質量約地球的0.4至1.4倍。</span>它們環繞「TRAPPIST-1」，距離地球約39光年（約368.94兆公里）。這個發現讓天文學家都十分雀躍，對於在太陽系外尋找外星生物，可能比預期得要快燃起希望。這也是第一次發現這麼多顆「可能有生命的行星」環繞同一顆恆星。<br />\n<br />\n「Trappist-1」比木星稍大一點，亮度比太陽還弱2千倍，由於這顆恆星小又冷，讓環繞它的7顆行星相當溫和，意味著可能蘊藏液態水，甚至是生命體。研究人員指，7顆中有3顆行星位於適居帶，其中行星「Trappist-1f」最有可能孕育生命體。雖然它的氣溫比地球還低一點，但若有適當的大氣層和足夠的溫室氣體就有可能宜居。<br />\n<br />\n瑞士伯爾尼大學教授德莫里（Brice-Olivier Demory）認為，<span style=\"color: red;\">這七顆行星是迄今尋找外星生命的首選。</span> 而參與研究的比利時列日大學天體物理學家吉倫（Michael Gillon）則相信，「Trappist-1」周圍可能有更多行星。（國際中心／綜合外電報導）<br />\n<br />\n好似真係好屈機 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/oh.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n唔掂喎咁低溫..."},{"pid":"4332fd5dfa05f133f19510f8680150fa0001bc2a","tid":130990,"uid":6777,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-23T02:40:58.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>美國航太總署（NASA）和比利時研究團隊周三（22日）宣布這個消息，<span style=\"color: red;\">這7顆行星位於水瓶座，大小、質量與地球差不多，半徑約地球的0.8至1.1倍，質量約地球的0.4至1.4倍。</span>它們環繞「TRAPPIST-1」，距離地球約39光年（約368.94兆公里）。這個發現讓天文學家都十分雀躍，對於在太陽系外尋找外星生物，可能比預期得要快燃起希望。這也是第一次